# Generated working/derived data. Regenerable from data/raw/ plus the
# tracked review/ CSVs, so not committed.
# reports/ is intentionally NOT ignored -- generated citizen-readable reports
# are the project's public-facing output and are meant to be committed.
#
# data/raw/ is intentionally NOT ignored either: source documents are public
# government records, and committing them makes extraction independently
# verifiable against the original. See docs/methodology.md "Preserve" and
# the raw-record storage policy note there. If a record is ever acquired
# that is not itself public (should not normally happen for this project),
# do not commit it -- add a specific exclusion instead of reverting this.
data/interim/
data/processed/

